[Patient] What should I eat to help my heart failure?
[Educator] Focus on fruits, veggies, whole grains, lean proteins, and low-fat dairy for a healthy heart.
[Patient] Where can I find these foods in my neighborhood?
[Educator] Look for local markets or grocery stores with fresh produce. Community gardens may also help.
[Patient] I'm used to eating certain foods, can I still enjoy them?
[Educator] Try modifying recipes to make them heart-healthy. I can provide you with some ideas.
[Patient] What if I can't afford healthy foods?
[Educator] I can help you find local food assistance programs or online grocery delivery services. 
[Patient] Will changing my diet really make a difference in my heart health?
[Educator] Yes, a heart-healthy diet can improve your overall health and quality of life. Start small changes.